  "text": "The extremal formulation by Gorodezky and Pak [CITATION_1] is the following. Each arc e is associated with a (distinct) random variable which is present with probability 1 − p a . A cluster is a subset of vertices not containing r so that no arc is going out. We want all vertices to be able to reach r. Thus clusters are undesirable. However, Condition 1 is not satisfied if we simply let the bad events be clusters. Instead, we choose minimal clusters to be bad events.",
